Package: kapsis
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 3.2), git (>= 1:2.0), jq, podman (>= 4.0) | docker.io
Recommends: yq
Description: Hermetically isolated AI agent sandbox
 Kapsis is a sandbox orchestration platform for running multiple AI coding
 agents (Claude Code, Aider, Codex, Gemini) in parallel with complete
 isolation via Podman containers and Copy-on-Write filesystems.
 .
 Features:
  - Multi-agent support with parallel execution
  - Podman-based container isolation with rootless execution
  - Copy-on-Write filesystem isolation using overlays
  - Git worktree integration for parallel branch development
  - Maven isolation with snapshot blocking
  - Centralized logging and status reporting
